{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What boats are available?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We offer three exceptional vessels: Day Tripper (14-person boat) perfect for intimate groups and small birthday parties, featuring a licensed captain, premium sound, coolers with ice, and comfortable seating, starting at $200/hour with a 4-hour minimum. Meeseeks and The Irony (25-person boat) is our most popular choice for medium groups of 18-25 guests, ideal for bachelor and bachelorette parties, featuring professional captain and crew, premium Bluetooth sound, and large coolers with ice, starting at $225/hour with a 4-hour minimum. Clever Girl (50-person flagship) is our spectacular flagship vessel featuring 14 disco balls and a giant Texas flag, accommodating 30-50 guests with professional crew and premium amenities, starting at $250/hour with a 4-hour minimum, perfect for corporate events and large celebrations."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's included in each package?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Standard Package includes professional captain and crew, large coolers (bring your own ice), premium Bluetooth sound system, clean restroom facilities, sun and shade seating, and is fully BYOB friendly (cans/plastic only). Essentials Package (+$100-200/hour based on boat) includes everything from Standard PLUS coolers pre-stocked with ice, 5-gallon insulated water dispenser, solo cups and ice water, 6-foot folding table for food, and vendor coordination for catering. Ultimate Package (+$250-350/hour based on boat) includes everything from Essentials PLUS giant lily pad float, guest of honor float (unicorn or ring), disco ball cups, bubble guns and bubble wands, champagne flutes and fruit juices, SPF-50 spray sunscreen, plates, plasticware, paper towels, and full party atmosphere setup."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can we bring food and drinks?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes! We are fully BYOB friendly (21+ with valid ID required). You can bring your own beer, wine, seltzers, and non-alcoholic beverages in cans or plastic containers only - no glass allowed for safety. Feel free to bring snacks, meals, or coordinate catering with our help. We provide large coolers and cups. With our Essentials Package, coolers come pre-stocked with ice, and with the Ultimate Package, we also include champagne flutes, plates, plasticware, and a 6-foot folding table for your food setup."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does pricing work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We believe in transparent, straightforward pricing with no hidden fees. Your base cost is calculated simply: Hourly rate × Duration = Base cost. Day Tripper starts at $200/hour, Meeseeks and The Irony starts at $225/hour, and Clever Girl starts at $250/hour (all with 4-hour minimums). Package upgrades are added per hour: Essentials Package adds $100-200/hour depending on boat size, Ultimate Package adds $250-350/hour depending on boat size. Additional crew fees apply for larger groups: $50/hour for 26-30 guests, $100/hour for 51-75 guests. We add 8.25% tax to the total, and a 20% gratuity for the crew is suggested but not required."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are the crew fees?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Additional crew fees apply based on your party size to ensure exceptional service and safety. For groups of 26-30 guests, an additional crew member is required at $50/hour. For larger groups of 51-75 guests, additional crew support is required at $100/hour. These fees ensure you have adequate professional staff to manage your event safely and provide the best experience for all guests."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How far in advance should we book?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "We recommend booking as early as possible, especially for weekend dates. Popular weekend dates typically fill up 6-8 weeks in advance, particularly during peak season (April-September). For weekday bookings or off-peak times, you may have more flexibility. If you're planning a special event like a bachelor/bachelorette party, corporate event, or milestone birthday, we suggest reaching out 2-3 months ahead to secure your preferred date and boat."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do deposits and payments work?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "25% deposit if >30 days out (balance due 30 days prior). If booking within 30 days, 50% deposit due and remainder within 72 hours."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What's your cancellation policy?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "48-hour full refund window after booking. After that, cancellations are weather-dependent at the captain's discretion. Pro‑rated refunds if weather shortens the cruise."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is swimming allowed?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, when conditions are safe and at the captain's discretion. Life jackets are on board and available for swimming - we encourage guests to wear them for safety."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What about life jackets?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Adult life jackets are provided. Infant/child life jackets must be brought by guests."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can we customize our route?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Absolutely! You have complete control over your Lake Travis experience. Work with your captain to customize your route, timing, and activities. Want to anchor at a quiet cove for swimming? Prefer to cruise around Devil's Cove and see the party scene? Looking for scenic spots for photos? Your captain will work with you to create the perfect itinerary for your group. We can also help coordinate with local vendors for catering, photography, or other services to make your event exactly what you envision."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are private charters family-friendly with kids welcome?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — private charters welcome guests of every age. Kids, parents, grandparents, family reunions, anniversary celebrations, school graduations, and milestone birthdays are all common bookings. The shared public ATX Disco Cruise has stricter age requirements because it is a multi-group BYOB party environment, but a private charter is your own boat with your own guest list. Children's life jackets in all sizes are on every boat. We never permit underage drinking, but family events with non-alcoholic beverages are fully welcome."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can we book a private charter for an anniversary or quiet sunset cruise?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes — anniversaries, micro-weddings, vow renewals, intimate milestone birthdays, and executive retreats are some of our most popular quiet-mode bookings. The same fleet that powers a 75-guest disco celebration can host a 14-guest sunset anniversary on the Day Tripper with your own playlist, your own decor, and a calm Hill Country backdrop. Our crew adjusts the vibe to match the occasion — high-energy when you want it, calm and curated when you need it."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What does Premier include that a DIY pontoon rental doesn't?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every private charter includes a US Coast Guard licensed captain (you don't drive or navigate), professional crew, premium marine-grade Bluetooth sound system, large coolers with ice, lily pad and unicorn floats at the swim stop, climate-controlled restrooms, shaded lounges, premium add-on packages (Mimosa Cooler, Sparkle, Bride/Groom Spotlight), tax and 20% gratuity included in the quote, and free reschedules for any weather-caused cancellation. A DIY pontoon rental at $400-$800/day requires you to drive, navigate, bring music, rent floats, haul coolers, and coordinate everything yourself — by the time you add what's missing, Premier almost always wins on total cost AND on effort saved."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the safety record of Premier Party Cruises?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Operating since 2009 — 15+ years on Lake Travis. 150,000+ guests served. Perfect safety record (zero reportable incidents). 100% US Coast Guard licensed captains (Merchant Mariner Credential). 100% CPR-certified crew on every sailing. 4.9/5.0 average rating across hundreds of reviews. Every boat is inspected before every sailing on a documented schedule. Every sailing begins with a signature Premier safety welcome ritual covering life jackets, emergency exits, weather policy, and swim stops. Children's life jackets in all sizes on every boat."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are private charters available year-round?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Private charters operate every day of the year, 12 months a year. Central Texas has mild winters so cruising stays comfortable most days. Off-peak months (November through February) actually offer better availability, more date flexibility, and a more exclusive lake experience — many corporate groups, families, and intimate celebrations prefer them. The seasonal window (March 1 – October 31) only applies to the shared public ATX Disco Cruise, not to private charters."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How do the Standard, Essentials, and Ultimate packages differ?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Every private charter includes Standard amenities by default: Coast Guard licensed captain + crew, premium marine-grade Bluetooth audio, large coolers (always BYOB), sun + shade seating, climate-controlled restrooms, fully BYOB-friendly setup. Essentials Package adds: coolers pre-stocked with ice, 5-gallon water dispenser, solo cups and ice water, 6-foot folding table for food, and vendor coordination for catering (+$100 on Day Tripper, +$150 on Meeseeks/Irony, +$200 on Clever Girl). Ultimate Package adds everything in Essentials plus: giant 6×20 ft lily pad float, guest-of-honor float (unicorn or ring), disco ball cups, bubble guns + wands, champagne flutes + juices, SPF-50 spray sunscreen, plates + plasticware + paper towels, full party atmosphere setup (+$250 / +$300 / +$350 by boat size). Either package turns a Standard private charter into a fully all-inclusive experience."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can Party On Delivery set up our drinks before we board?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. Premier's sister company Party On Delivery takes your BYOB order (beer, wine, seltzers, spirits, mixers, ice — cans and plastic only, no glass) and delivers it straight to the boat with everything set up and iced down when you arrive. You get retail prices (no marina markup) plus 100% buyback on unopened bottles — only pay for what you drink. This is the easiest way to do BYOB on Lake Travis: you step on, drinks are already cold and ready. Food delivery can be coordinated too."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is BYOB always required or is there a bar option?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "BYOB is always the alcohol model on Premier Party Cruises — this keeps prices dramatically lower than bar-service boats and lets you bring exactly what your group wants. Cans and plastic containers only (no glass, for safety). If you'd rather not shop or haul coolers, our sister company Party On Delivery handles the entire BYOB setup for you at retail prices with 100% buyback on unopened bottles. Bartender service is available as an add-on for private charters (not bachelor/bachelorette parties) at $600 per party — the bartender mixes and serves from the BYOB supply you or Party On Delivery bring."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is a private charter quiet enough for an anniversary or corporate retreat?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. A private charter is your boat for your vibe — you set the music, volume, and pace. Most of our private bookings are actually NOT party-mode: anniversaries, micro-weddings, corporate client entertainment, family reunions, retirement celebrations, and executive retreats all run on the same fleet with a quiet sunset cruise template. Premium Bluetooth audio means you can play soft background music or an executive playlist just as easily as a DJ-style party mix. We explicitly support what we call 'Two-Mode Vibe': Disco for party, Chill for quiet. Both get the same captain, crew, safety standards, and Lake Travis scenery."
      }
    }
  ]
